class Solution {
    public int findChampion(int n, int[][] edges) {
        int[] degree = new int[n];
        for (int[] e : edges) {
            degree[e[1]]++;
        }
        int champion = -1;
        for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
            if (degree[i] == 0) {
                if (champion == -1) {
                    champion = i;
                } else {
                    return -1;
                }
            }
        }
        return champion;
    }
}
```

In this code, we first calculate the indegree of each node. An indegree of a node in a DAG is the number of edges pointing towards it. In the tournament context, an indegree of 0 indicates that the team is the weakest team (i.e., no team is stronger than it). If we find a node with indegree 0, we set it as the champion and if we find another node with indegree 0, we return -1 because there are multiple champions. If no team is the champion, we return -1.

