class Solution {
    public long maximumSubarraySum(int[] nums, int k) {
        long ans = Long.MIN_VALUE;
        long sum = 0;
        Map<Integer, Long> minS = new HashMap<>();
        for (int x : nums) {
            long s1 = minS.getOrDefault(x - k, Long.MAX_VALUE / 2);
            long s2 = minS.getOrDefault(x + k, Long.MAX_VALUE / 2);
            ans = Math.max(ans, sum + x - Math.min(s1, s2));
            minS.merge(x, sum, Math::min);
            sum += x;
        }
        return ans > Long.MIN_VALUE / 4 ? ans : 0;
    }
}
```

The code is calculating the maximum sum of a good subarray of nums. A subarray is good if the absolute difference between its first and last element is exactly k. The code uses a map to keep track of the minimum sum of subarrays ending at each number, and calculates the maximum sum of a good subarray by subtracting the minimum sum of subarrays ending at x - k and x + k from the sum of subarrays ending at x. If the calculated sum is greater than the current maximum, it is updated.

