class Solution {
    public long flowerGame(int n, int m) {
        long a = (long)m * n;
        long b = ((long)m/2) * ((long)n-((long)n/2));
        return a + b;
    }
}
```

This solution first calculates the total number of possible pairs by multiplying the number of flowers in the clockwise and anti-clockwise directions. It then calculates the number of pairs where Alice wins by subtracting the number of pairs where Bob wins. Bob wins if the number of flowers in the clockwise direction is even. The number of such pairs is half the number of flowers in the anti-clockwise direction times the number of flowers in the clockwise direction.

