This problem can be solved by using a binary indexed tree (BIT). We firstly sort the array and then calculate the prefix sum of the array. After that, we iterate through the array and update the BIT at index j with the maximum value between the current value and the sum of the current number and the prefix sum at index j - 1. At last, we return the maximum value in the BIT.

